The paper discusses a debugging approach for Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of logic programming and non-monotonic reasoning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category. The paper also focuses on the syntax and semantics of ASP, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper proposes a user-friendly graphical interface, which indicates that it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the empirical analysis of the new debugger, which could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
